<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><b>PANEL DISCUSSION FROM SOCIALISM 2007</b></font><br>
<font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="5"><b>Confronting empire</b></font><p>
<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">June 22, 2007 | Pages 8 to 12</font><p>

<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><b><a href="636_08_Wasfi.shtml">PREVIOUS SPEAKER</a> | <a href="636_08_Scahill.shtml">NEXT SPEAKER</a></b><br>
<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><a href="636_08_Pilger.shtml">John Pilger</a> | <a href="636_08_Sanchez.shtml">Mart&iacute;n Sanchez</a> | <a href="636_08_Wasfi.shtml">Dahlia Wasfi</a> | <a href="636_08_Mejia.shtml">Camilo Mej&iacute;a</a> | <a href="636_08_Scahill.shtml">Jeremy Scahill</a> | <a href="636_08_Will.shtml">Rob Will</a> | <a href="636_08_Geier.shtml">Joel Geier</a><p>
<p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1">- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -</font></p>

<font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="5"><b>Camilo Mej&iacute;a</b></font><p>

<font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="2"><i>First soldier to go public with his refusal to redeploy to Iraq, court-martialed and imprisoned for seven months, and author of the new book </i><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/redirect.html?ie=UTF8&amp;location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FRoad-Ar-Ramadi-Rebellion-Sergeant%2Fdp%2F1595580522%3Fie%3DUTF8%26s%3Dbooks%26qid%3D1182362924%26sr%3D1-1&amp;tag=socialistwork-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325" target="_blank">Road from Ar Ramadi</a>, <i>about his experiences.</i></font><p>

<font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="3">I WANT to start by sharing with you a passage from my book. This was after an ambush, and we went to the site to look for evidence. It was a moment of reflection while was in Iraq.<p>
I was fascinated by how different Iraqi life was from our own back home, and wanted to find out more. The cultural differences were many, beginning with the language and religion, which seemed to dominate their lives.<p>

